        "title": "build: enable modern TypeScript flags",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Update @typescript/native-preview to 7.0.0-dev.20260524.1.\n- Enable erasableSyntaxOnly, isolatedModules, verbatimModuleSyntax, and useDefineForClassFields.\n- Refactor TypeScript syntax blockers across core, plugins, SDK, and UI: parameter properties, type-only imports, const enums, and class-field declarations.\n\n## Verification\n\n- .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local\n- env -u OPENCLAW_TESTBOX pnpm check:changed\n- pnpm build\n- git diff --check\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Modern TypeScript compiler options can now typecheck and build against the repository without relying on non-erasable TypeScript syntax or legacy class-field semantics.\nReal environment tested: Local macOS checkout on Node/pnpm repo defaults.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: env -u OPENCLAW_TESTBOX pnpm check:changed; pnpm build; git diff --check; .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local.\nEvidence after fix: check:changed completed typecheck, lint, and runtime import-cycle checks successfully; build-all completed tsdown, runtime postbuild, plugin SDK dts/export checks, and UI production build successfully; autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\nObserved result after fix: The full changed gate and production build pass with the new TS flags enabled.\nWhat was not tested: Full cross-platform or live provider scenarios; this is a compile/tooling modernization with local build and changed-gate proof.\n",
